# JetBrains Software Licenses

As a student you are eligible for free software licenses from many companies, including JetBrains.

This cluster, and others, use their software as the primary IDE, and as such, other IDEs many have very limited support.

During your study we strongly recommend you use the environment provided to you over your own systems to limit interruption and excessive time spent by lecturers to solve software based issues.

> **BYOD:** Remember that BYOD are only supported by the lecturer at their discretion, and generally by appointment outside of contact time.

They will send you two emails with links, which you need to click and follow and complete the pages as needed.

When it co0mes up with a login screen, fill out the form with your email address, and a dummy password.

This will send another email with a confirm your account link.

Opening this allows you to complete the form and then have your licenses credited.

When you open any of their products, you will be able to register using the email address and password.

## JetBrains at Home

When at home, we seriously recommend you downloading and installing the JetBrains Toolbox. This software allows you to install, uninstall and maintain the most up to date versions of the JetBrains Software, including PHP Storm, the IDE of choice for this and the SAAS-BED Clusters.
